        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:34PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Big Sandy to 20 miles
south of St. Pierre to 20 miles northeast of Geraldine to 10 miles
northwest of Denton. Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Big Sandy, Winifred, Azure, Parker School, Agency, St. Pierre,
Sangrey, Boneau, Rocky Boy, Suffolk, Square Butte, Lloyd, Judith
Landing, Christina, and Iliad.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
